body:
@danielmorrison, @ersatzryan, right, I see. If it's breaking stuff it definitely makes it more pressing :+1:

@ersatzryan default to 3 instead of 0 according to the de facto standard set by browsers as @jamesotron in the other thread, so it's not arbitrary, the choices is clearly between 0 or 3 here.

I think for the looking forward, 3 is a more reasonable default than 0, especially when it has the bonus points of being inline with what browsers do. Ultimately if there's way to change this, I don't think most people would mind it one way or the other.

It guess I don't object using global variables, seeing how that's what we do currently, just wanted to take this opportunity to brainstorm on the longer term fix here, but I guess it's not a blocker.

Perhaps the best thing to do is declare this 28ab79d a regression, revert it for 4.0.1, and add the config for 4.1 with a default of 3.

@jeremy?
